                  <div align="left"> 
                    <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4">
                       <tr> 
                        <td height="63"><img src="../global/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="1"> 
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" height="8" width="100%" colspan="3"><span class="header">Mission Madness #2</span></td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#333399" height="2" width="41%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="1%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="58%" bgcolor="#FF9C00"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN=2><SPAN CLASS="header">Rating </SPAN><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/rating/9.gif" BORDER=0></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=22"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=22"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=5538">Bart "Bartman" McLeroy</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Description</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%"><span class=text>With some strategic mission selection and a little pre-planning, your missions can be worth more than you think.</span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Article</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>We all know the traditional ways to boost points from a mission you&#146;ve solved: Assign Mission Specialists, Particle Fountain, Drought Tree, and the 62nd Rule of Acquisition are good sources of bonus points.  But what if you didn&#146;t have to use up a valuable card play to get bonus points from a mission?  With some strategic mission selection and a little pre-planning, your missions can be worth more than you think.<br>
<br>
Geological Survey is, at first blush, a fairly lightweight mission.  Only worth a measly 20 points, it wouldn&#146;t make its way into many decks.  However, if you have 3 Geology or 3 Greed present, the mission is worth 10 additional points.  All affiliations have access to a very skilled geologist, Mortal Q (Geology x10), and several affiliations, most notably the Ferengi, have multiple personnel with the Greed skill.  A mission with a similar attribute is A Good Day to Live.  A 30 point mission with very unique requirements (Kang, Kor or Koloth), you get an extra 5 points for each member of the Blood Oath gang in your away team.  Using Blood Oath you can increase the number of personnel with the Red, right-pointing Nemesis icon and further boost your score when you solve this mission.<br>
<br>
Reunion also gives you variable point values based on members of your away team.  Unlike the previous two missions, the point value of this one is entirely dependent on who you bring to the attempt.  Considering its strict mission requirements (Cantankerousness, Miracle Worker, or Spock) making it through the attempt with all three is certainly worth the 40 point reward.<br>
<br>
Investigate Incursion is somewhat unique in that the point value for you is variable, but fixed (at 30 points) for your opponent.  The mission is worth at least 30 points for you.  If any Borg affiliation card, card with a Borg-only icon, or a Borg Ship dilemma is at the mission, the value of the mission increases to 45 points.  If you happen to be playing against a Borg opponent, the extra points from the mission contain a disadvantage.  Text on your opponent&#146;s side of the mission allows them to report their Borg ships with crew at that location.<br>
<br>
The next two missions give bonuses for having particular equipment cards present.  Cure Blight provides an additional 5 points if a Medical-related equipment card is present.  If you take the trouble to earn the Sword of Kahless (admittedly an Artifact, but it is used as an equipment card) you can later get a 10 point bonus for completing Bat&#146;leth Tournament using the Sword as your bat&#146;leth.<br>
<br>
The following missions provide bonuses as a reward for discarding equipment cards.  Purchase Moon has a value ranging from 10 to 40 points, depending on how many Gold-Pressed Latinum you are willing to discard (between 1 and 4). With the 1st Rule of Acquisition in play, you can later download those same Latinum from your discard pile. Like Investigate Incursion, the mission is worth a fixed number of points (30) to your opponent, who must discard 3 Latinum to solve it.  Kressari Rendezvous is worth a base 25 points, but you can discard up to four hand weapons when the mission is completed and get a 5 point bonus for each one.<br>
<br>
Our last mission is quite unique.  Patrol Neutral Zone is worth 10X points, where X is the number of Neutral Zone locations in play.  Whereas the other missions examined in this article provide bonus points contingent on you performing a particular action or bringing cards to the mission, the value of a PNZ is determined both by your missions and those of your opponent.  An additional twist is Commander Charvanek, released in the Mirror, Mirror expansion.  Once in play, X=3 on every Patrol Neutral Zone mission, regardless of the other Neutral Zone missions in play or if it has already been solved.  <br>
<br>
In Mission Madness #3, I will take a look at missions that can help you control your opponent&#146;s actions.  See you then!<br>
<br>
Missions reviewed in this article:<br>
<br>
Geological Survey (Universal, Alpha Quadrant, Planet, PSII)<br>
<br>
A Good Day to Live (Unique, Alpha Quadrant, Planet, BoG)<br>
<br>
Reunion (Unique, Alpha Quadrant, Planet, AU)<br>
<br>
Investigate Incursion (Universal, Alpha Quadrant, Space, OTSD)<br>
<br>
Cure Blight (Unique, Gamma Quadrant, Planet, DS9)<br>
<br>
Bat&#146;leth tournament (Universal, Alpha Quadrant, Planet, BoG)<br>
<br>
Purchase Moon (Unique, Alpha Quadrant, Planet, RoA)<br>
<br>
Kressari Rendezvous (Unique, Alpha Quadrant, Space, DS9)<br>
<br>
Patrol Neutral Zone (Universal, Alpha Quadrant, Space, FC) </span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=22"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=22"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><a href="articles.php3"><img src="/stccg/global/images/back.gif" border="0" ></a></TD><TD><a href="articleprint.php3?article=22" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="/stccg/global/images/print.gif" border="0"></a></TD></TR></TABLE>
